  "title": "Allow listening for events on searchBox (regular JS / non-react version)",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\nIt is related to https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2017\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\nI would like to be able to use onSubmit in the regular JS / non-react version of instantsearch.js\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\nI'm trying to make https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/1450#issuecomment-259118772 happen so I tried to do \r\n\r\n```js\r\ndocument.querySelector('.ais-SearchBox-form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {\r\n    console.log('tried to submit');\r\n    e.preventDefault();\r\n    document.querySelector('.ais-SearchBox-input').blur();\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut it won't work. I'm guessing because there is already a preventDefault in instantsearch.js but I also tried it without a preventDefault and it still won't work.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThank you @Haroenv for suggesting I'd make a new issue\r\n",
